cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.DS, cs.CV, cs.NE 

This paper is likely to belong to the category of cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it proposes a new algorithm to enhance the accuracy and efficiency of gradient boosting using more complex base learners. It also discusses optimization techniques to speed up the algorithm. 

It could also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as gradient boosting is a popular technique in AI and the paper proposes a new approach to improve it. 

cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is another possible category as the paper discusses the use of decision trees as base learners and proposes a new type of decision tree. 

cs.CV (Computer Vision) is a possible category as gradient boosting is often used in computer vision applications and the paper discusses the use of decision trees for regression. 

Finally, cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is a possible category as gradient boosting is a type of ensemble learning, which is related to neural networks and evolutionary algorithms.
